inn1.comm: gets bat on ball straightaway, full outside off and driven straight to cover
gets an outside edge this time and it drops well short of second slip, he gets a hand to it though
gets across and punches it firmly down to cover
keeps it slightly full, Jamshed moves across and pushes it down to mid-off
had to hurry that single, inside edge to the pads and the ball rolls to the off side, Hafeez was off the blocks quickly but Jamshed wasn't so quick
gives him width and slightly short too, punched towards cover
gets a bit of away swing and he stays back and knocks it to the on side
it was a checked drive but boy it travelled quickly, fullish on the pads and Jamshed punched it uppishly on the front foot and it was well wide of mid-on
drifts on the pads and he whips it away down to deep square leg, fine leg comes across and mops up
gets across his stumps and drives it straight
excellent stop by Maxwell at point, he flung himself to his left and deflected it to cover
pushes it to the off side
good length on the off stump and he safely leaves it alone
this time he misdirects it on his pads and Hafeez works it off his pads and the ball races to fine leg
attempting the yorker again and it's another low full, worked off his pads and straight to fine leg
gets beside the line and steers it straight to cover
gets back and across and works it to mid-on
appeal for an lbw, it was full and swinging in, hits the base of the pads as he tries to clip it away, missing leg
full and wide and driven straight to cover, bowler was lucky to get away with that

another confident shout for lbw and Clarke's asked for the review, the umpire gave it not out, the ball landed outside the leg stump and hit his front pad and it appeared like missing leg anyway, Bowden wasn't convinced, Clarke took his time and Australia have wasted a review
moves across his stumps and punches it towards mid-on
shorter in length and he gets an outside edge to third man and there's a direct hit at the batsman's end, Jamshed was home, the third umpire took a look
full on the pads and clipped just wide of mid-on for a single
comes round the wicket, he gets across and jams a full delivery towards cover
gets beside the line and steers him down to deep point
holds the length back to Hafeez, he stays back and defends solidly

soft dismissal! He hits it straight to short extra cover, it was on a good length outside off and Hafeez stabbed at it, didn't go through with the shot and it lobbed straight to David Hussey, Hafeez's ordinary one-day form continues
and Azhar has a close call! Lovely delivery shaping in from a good length, he was forward to drive but the ball bounced a bit more than he expected
shapes it back in and Azhar leaves it alone to the keeper
fullish outside off and driven to the off side
drifts on the pads and he works it down to square leg
gets across his stumps and he defends to the off side
bit uncharacteristic from Azhar but safe nonetheless, it was short and wide outside off, really wide and he slashed that over the slips and one bounce to the third man boundary
he bowls it full and wide outside off and Azhar drives but takes his hand off the bat as he pushe s it past cover
full on the pads and he worked away to deep midwicket

and another soft dismissal! Chipped to mid-on, it was shaping in full on the pads and Azhar was looking to chip it over the on side, the trouble was the bat turned as he made contact and hence mistimed it, Johnson jogged to his right and caught it on the fall
too short and wide and Shafiq reached out and slapped that in front of square, past cover and the ball slowed down before it reached the rope
this swung in and landed full on the pads and he drilled it down the track
tried to flick this away and the bat turned and couldn't time it, managed to beat the infield though
gets beside the line and punches it square on the packed off-side field
comes forward and drives him towards cover
a false shot there, it was slightly short and wide and Shafiq couldn't resist a slash, lucky not to get an edge
Starc working up a nice angle across the right-hander, he was forward to drive and the ball fizzed past the edge
full and wide outside off and he mistimed the drive towards point
this time he was across his stumps early enough to cover the line, softly pushed down to mid-off
shortish and wide outside off and he punches it straight to cover
full on the stumps and he gets behind the line and pushes it to the off side
this time he clips it across the line to midwicket, nicely timed
good delivery from over the wicket, outside off and luring him to drive, he nearly got an outside edge to the keeper
fuller delivery and he gets some bat on the drive, pushes it towards point
gets an outside edge on the drive and the ball goes to third man
gets across and knocks it down the pitch
full outside the off stump and driven to the off side
that should come as a relief for Pakistan, it was a half volley outside the off stump and Jamshed was forward and pushed it wide of cover
even better, this was outside the off stump as well and enough width for Jamshed to slice it past point and cover, pure timing there
bowls it straighter this time and he punches it to mid-off

good comeback by Starc and better reflexes from Wade! Starc hit the deck harder this time to vary his length, there was extra bounce which Jamshed wasn't ready for, he tried to fend it off outside the off stump but the ball took the top half of the bat and Wade jumped to his left and took it
pokes at it outside off and the ball misses the edge
defends the ball drops towards the keeper
firm drive and Warner does well to dive to his left and stop it
stays back and punches it towards mid-on
reaches out to drive and he mistimes it back to the bowler
goes back and punches it to the on side
punches it firmly down to long-on
tossed up wide outside off and driven wide of cover
drops it short of a length and he rocks back and punches it to deep cover
gets across the stumps and safely defends it
punched down the track and Hussey does well to dive to his right and stop it
he brings out the reverse sweep but doesn't time it well, third man picks up
gently tucked away off the pads
full on the pads and worked towards square leg
goes back and punches it back to the bowler
rocks back and punches it straight to cover
full on the stumps and drilled down the track
goes back and slaps it straight to cover
tries to drill it down the ground but Clarke gets across and stops it
very slow through the air, hits the pads outside the line of the stumps as he tries to flick
drills it down to the on side
gets an outside edge towards short third man
gets forward and pushes it to the off side
quicker delivery and he works it behind square on the on side
plays the lap shot, places it down to fine leg
goes back and cuts on the up and beats short third man
confusion in the calling, cuts to point and Misbah sends Shafiq back, the throw was wide to the bowler's end
gets well forward and drives towards long-off
tossed up on the pads and worked down to fine leg
loosener on the pads and he whips it away wide of square leg
not much pace on that one, gets beside the line and steers it just wide of Warner at point
cranks up his pace and Shafiq comes across and softly pushes it to cover
sweetly punched off the meat of the bat but straight to mid-off
that was pitched short and didn't bounce too much, he biffs it down to deep square leg
drifts on the pads and he clips it down to fine leg
fullish on the pads and he clips it wide of midwicket
tough chance for a caught and bowled! Driven on the up and Christian dived against the direction of his follow through and got a finger to it
goes across the stumps and punches it to the off side
gets his direction all wrong, full on the pads and Shafiq turned the bat and clipped it easily down to fine leg
on the pads again and he works it away wide of mid-on
comes across his stumps and punches it towards point
false line there, drifts on the pads and he whips it down to fine leg with the fielder up, didn't reach the rope, the fielder pulled it back
comes beside the line and he dabs it down to third man
well played by Misbah, a bit too straight and full on the pads, uses his wrists well and works it wide of midwicket, two fielders give chase
left alone to the keeper, not much bounce this time
tucked away off the pads and the fielder at backward square leg jogs and picks it up
sprays that full and wide outside off, he fails to jam out the yorker
fullish on the pads and he works it away down to mid-on
gets beside the line and slices it down to mid-off
chipped just wide of midwicket and they scamper through for a single
tucks him up for room and he opens the face and slices it to point
sliced away again, not much pace on the pitch so he was able to glide it to third man with ease
makes himself a lot of room this time and he can't slice it wide of point, good diving save
makes room and slices it down to the off side
gets beside the room and the ball comes back in off the pitch he dabs it towards point
Misbahj walks a long away across his stumps before the bowler delivers, tries to play it fine but can't beat short fine leg
drives with conviction down the ground, top shot, it was full on the stumps and he waited for it and drove through the line and beat mid-off, excellent straight drive
gets beside the line and chops it towards point
drops it towards point and thinks of a single but Shafiq wisely sends him back
gets across his stumps and punches it towards mid-off
Shafiq decides to take on Christain by hoicking him across the line wide of midwicket, the sweeper covers up
drifts on the pads and he clips it towards fine leg
stays beside the line and steers it down to third man, easily done
Misbah plays that slice really easily again, he doesn't have much room but manages to squeeze it wide of point
punched down to long-on for a single
bit wide and he slashed and missed
stays back and he slashed it wide of point
take that! Tossed up on middle and leg and he whams it with the turn over deep midwicket, lots of intent on that shot
pushes a single down to long-on
tries to dab it down to third man and the ball comes back in and nearly takes the edge
on the pads and worked away down to fine leg, uses his wrists well
keeps it nice and tight and he pushes it down the pitch
the ball skids through and he chops it down to point
slices it down to point again
on the pads and gently flicked to the on side, the keeper is still up to the stumps
teases him by tossing it very slowly, tries ti dab it away to third man but misses
drops it a bit short and he rocks back and chops it behind square on the off side
bit of turn this time, mistimes the drive back to the bowler
tucks it with the turn down to midwicket
stays back at the crease and cuts straight to point
very slow off the pitch and he cuts hard to the sweeper on the off side for a couple
gives him width and he stays beside it and chops it towards cover
tries to hoick him away and he mistimes it to long-on, Christian took a lot of pace off the ball
goes back at the crease and chops it towards mid-off

Christian breaks the stand and Misbah perishes trying to be aggressive, Christian took a lot of pace off the ball with his offcutter, the keeper was up to the stumps to stifle the batsman, Misbah tried to hoick it over the on side and got a thick inside edge to the stumps
short and wide and Umar gets off the mark with a cut to deep point
opens the face of the bat and dabs it down to third man
on the off stump. Umar Akmal leans forward and drives it to mid-off for a single
on the leg stump. Shafiq turns it to midwicket for a single
good length ball on the off stump. Umar Akmal looks to turn it and gets an outside edge that the keeper drops
comes forward and turns it to square-leg
short ball outside the off stump. Akmal cuts it to deep point for a single
good length ball outside the off stump. Umar comes forward and drives it to mid-off
fuller ball outside the off stump. Umar Akmal drives it to point
this shot has been a hallmark of his from U-19 days. Picks it from outside off and deposits it over deep midwicket for a six
runs it down to third-man for a single
fuller ball outside the off stump. Umar comes forward and drives it to mid-off
good length ball on the middle stump. Shafiq stands tall and turns it to midwicket for a single
wide ball outside the off stump. Shafiq looks to cut it and is beaten
comes forward and pushes it to mid-on for a single
off the outside edge to third-man for a boundary. Umar Akmal trying to get a hold on the things now
comes forward and drives it to mid-off for a single
and the charge is well and truly on. Shafiq comes down the track and lofts it to long-on for a six. In a matter of couple of overs, the scoring rate has changed
comes forward and pushes it to mid-on
fuller ball outside the off stump. Umar drives it to mid-off
short ball outside the off stump. Umar cuts it to point
on the leg stump. Umar turns it to midwicket for a couple
fuller ball on the leg stump. Umar Akmal turns it to fine-leg for a couple
forces it to deep midwicket for a single
short ball outside the off stump. Shafiq pulls it to short midwicket
walks across his stumps and works it to square leg, tells his partner to stay back
slower ball wide outside the off stump and he leans forward to drive past cover
tucked away with the angle towards deep midwicket
full on the off stump and drilled firmly down to cover
full again and driven very firmly down the ground to long-off
slower ball and he works it down to midwicket
goes over the top but he doesn't quite middle it, fetches that from off stump and  lofts across the line over mid-on, the fielder runs back and pulls it back
punched firmly down the track and Johnson runs across and pulls it back
tucks him up for room round the wicket, he punches it back to the bowler
bowls it straight again and it comes in with the angle, pushes it softly down to mid-off
sprays it wide outside the off stump and he reaches out and places it to third man
nearly edges it! Akmal was trying a cheeky dab to third man though there wasn't much width, could have feathered an edge
full and wide outside off and driven square of the wicket on the off side
the slower ball and Shafiq uses his wrists and works it down to long-on
turns the face of the bat and knocks it down to long-on
gets to his fifty with a flick for four! Stylishly played considering it was honing in on the yorker length, used his wrists and flicked it wide of fine leg
another full ball and hammered back to the bowler on the front foot
over deep extra cover! Johnson fires that from round the wicket and Umar Akmal made some room and lofted it crisply over the off side, it was an inside-out loft, not the easiest of shots
pushes it past the covers and gets off the strike
times that flick really well, fired on the pads and he whips it on the up and deep midwicket gives chase
mistimes the pull, fetched that from the off stump and the ball rolls to deep square leg
didn't come on too quickly, opened the face of the bat and gently dabbed it to third man
firmly punched down the ground to long-on and it's drinks
Starc comes round the wicket, sprays it wide outside off and Shafiq slashes and fails to make contact
full on the stumps and driven down the ground to long-on
Starc pitches it a bit short from round the wicket and Umar takes a couple of paces down the pitch and instead dabs it to third man
beats him with a fuller delivery this time, Umar pokes at it and nearly feathers an edge
angles it towards the stumps and he gets forward and drives to mid-off
full on the stumps and driven back to the bowler
starts off with a wide down the leg side, it's the first wide of the innings by the way
much better, bowls it straight and he softly punches it back to the bowler
makes a bit of room and tries to pinch it past the off side but he ends up chopping it to the covers
keeps it tight, hardly any room for Umar, he punches it on the front foot to cover
turning out to be a good over, bowls it on the middle stump and he can only push it back to the bowler
this was shorter and Umar did well to open the face and angle it to third man
tucks it away with the angle down to midwicket, end of a quiet over
fires it full on the leg stump from round the wicket and he drills it down the ground to long-on
Shafiq makes a lot of room to play an expansive drive through cover, doesn't find the gap though

and the start of the Powerplay brings a wicket! Shafiq was trying to repeat the shot from the previous ball, made a lot of room to spank it through cover, Starc fired it full and on the stumps from round the wicket, Shafiq made no contact and lost his stumps
bangs it in short down the leg side and wide called
gets off the mark with a flick down to square leg
fires it full on the pads and he drills it down the ground to long-on
once again drifts too much on the pads and helped on its way to fine leg
keeps it tight and on the stumps, defended back to the bowler
angled towards point and warner does really well to fling himself to his right save at least a couple
punched away to the off side but he can't beat cover, Pakistan looking to break free here
yet another dot ball, cramps him up for room and he pushes it straight to cover point
manages to pinch a single this time, opens the face and knocks it down to third man
bit of an anticlimax, Pattinson loses complete control of that one and sprays it well wide of the leg stump, work for Wade who does well
hammers a full ball straight back to the bowler
fires that full from round the wicket, he squirts it down to cover point
fires that full again and he drills it down to mid-on
oh well he misses out on a low full toss, he made a bit of room and tried to drive it through the off side and he missed it completely
tries to slash this one and he's beaten again
turning out to be yet another silent over! Umar can;t get bat on ball on this yorker outside the off stump
down the leg side and close to being called a wide, it's another scoring opportunity missed and it's a maiden!
goes back and slaps it straight to point
tucks it with the angle off his pads and he can't get it past backward square leg
swings his bat and connects very well  but there's protection at deep midwicket to pick it up
short of a length and he slaps it hard but the placement isn't good enough to beat point
another dot ball, gentlemen! Tucks him up for room and he punches it hard and straight to mid-off
keeps it on the off stump and he can only slap it straight to cover

that's the kind of improvisation that was needed, Starc was bowling round the wicket, Umar went right across his stumps and played a cheeky paddle scoop over short fine leg, first boundary in 42 balls
lucky to get away with a low full toss outside off, he can only push it to short third man

very soft dismissal in the end! Starc pitched it on a good length from round the wicket, Kamran was trying to tuck it over the on side but he ended up playing it too early and tamely chipped it to Clarke at midwicket
pitches it a bit short and he opens the face and dabs it down to third man

gone first ball! Clever move to bring in a slip because he has hit it straight there! Starc went back to over the wicket for Afridi, pitched it up on the off stump and drew him forward to drive, thick outside edge to Clarke, great captaincy and Starc has four wickets
lands it outside off and he safely leaves it alone
nicely played, it was a chipped drive over the bowler, not enough in it to travel to the rope, he gets to his fifty as well
he opens the face of the bat and steers it down to third man
shapes away from the left-hander and he leaves it alone
stays beside the line and he chops it down to point
sprays it on the pads and he whips it towards midwicket, the fielder gets a hand to it
bangs it in short and he swivels and pulls, mistimes it to the on side

Starc picks up five! Starc continues his round the wicket line to Umar Akmal, he sprays it full and wide and invites the lofted shot, Umar made room and tried to clear the infield but didn't get the elevation, straight to Bailey at cover
Ajmal leaves this one to the keeper, moves away off the surface
wide outside off and close to being called a wide
pitched up and tempts him to go for the drive, he nearly edges it
keeps it outside the off stump and he leaves it alone
Pakistan will hope for more of those, strayed on the pads and easily worked it away wide of the keeper
pushes it towards mid-on
the decline continues! Poor shot by Tanvir, not sure what he was attempting there, made room and tried to scoop it over mid-on, miscued it and Hussey ran across to his right and took a simple catch
drifts down the leg side from round the wicket, Cheema turned at the crease and the ball clipped the pads and raced to fine leg
turns at the crease and clips it with the angle down to fine leg
bangs it in short from round the wicket, swivels and miscues the pull but there was nobody at square leg
moves away after pitching and nearly kissed the face of the bat as he tried to run it down to third man
Pakistan are living off these gifts at the moment! Another full ball swinging on the pads and the ball clips the pads and runs away to fine leg
this time he bowls it short enough and wide for Ajmal to slap it past cover and point
solid defence this time, keeps it out in front of the stumps
nearly drags it back on to the stumps, short fine leg comes across and picks it up
gives him width and he chops it straight to point

He's been given lbw but Ajmal is reviewing it, it was full and swinging in on the pads, landed outside off and hit his pads as he tried to work it away off the pads, Bowden raised the finger, replays showed the ball missing leg stump so he survives
outside edge and just dropped short of Clarke at first slip, it was full on the stumps and produced a leading edge
nicely tucked away off the pads and he gives the strike to Cheema
gets across his stumps and softly pushes it towards cover
well played, it was rising up on the off stump and he fended it off with soft hands
fullish and angling across him and punched towards point
comes round the wicket and brings the ball back in, beats him completely

well we didn't need the extra time after all! Pattinson fires it full and straight on the leg stump, Ajmal couldn't resist the big shot but played too early, the ball went straight through and pushed back the leg stump

inn2.comm: Tanvir lands it on a good length on the off stump and Warner pushes it to the off side
slides it wide down the leg side, Pakistan have already conceded their first wide, Australia bowled their first wide late into the innings
keeps it nice and straight and he punches it back to the bowler
drifts on the pads and he clips it to the on side
leaves the left-hander, angles across and left alone
gets across the stumps and Wade gets off the mark with a clip across the line to fine leg
moves it away and he punches it softly to cover
tossed up from round the wicket, pushed back to the bowler
gets forward and drives back to the bowler
tossed up on the leg stump and driven back to the bowler
shout for an lbw, that was tossed up and his the base of the pads, he was well forward, may have missed leg
gets well forward and defends
down the leg side and clipped to the on side
induces a false shot, it was a wide offering and Warner wanted to cut but didn't get across properly and swished at it
drifts on the pads and the ball deflects off his legs to the on side
flashy drive, not convincing but safe, he reached out to one that was wide of the off stump and the outside edge comfortable beat second slip
bowls it straight on the middle stump and he defends
beats him outside off! Kept a bit low and went underneath the bat
bad ball, too wide down the leg side, he couldn't have chased it even if he wanted to
gets across to defend but gets a thick inside edge to the pads
slashed away through the gap, gave him width and he cut it past point, Jamshed gave chase
gets forward and defends it
drifts down the leg side and clips his body
swing and a miss! Warner will not want to see the replay, tossed up on off and middle and he was down on his knee slogging against the spin, missed everything and hit the stumps
shuffles and tucks it with the turn to the on side
shuffles and clips it hard past midwicket
gets good carry through to the keeper, well left by Clarke outside the off stump
he slides down the leg side again, these wides won't help Pakistan's cause
keeps it straight and on the off stump, defended to the off side
that was a solid punch, on the pads and he showed the full face and timed it well and placed it just wide of mid-on, Afridi gives chase
crashed off the front foot! Full and wide and he reached out and drove past cover, Hafeez dived and got a hand to it but it wasn't enough
comes round the wicket and bowls from really wide of the crease and Clarke leaves it alone
angles it inwards and he safely leaves it alone
full on the leg stump and squirted to wide mid-on
walks down the track and punches it down to mid-on
flighted on middle and leg and he pushes it to the on side
goes back and punches it softly to the off side
flighted down the leg side and clipped away to fine leg where Tanvir fields
makes a little room and pushes a full delivery down to mid-on
keeps it on the off stump and he stays back and defends towards mid-off
cracking shot, it was a length delivery which shaped away from the off stump and Clarke was right behind it to punch it past cover, solid timing
strays on the pads and he clips it wide of Afridi at midwicket
keeps it outside the off stump and he safely leaves it alone
close call for Clarke as he gets an inside edge on the drive onto his pads
shapes away from him and he safely leaves it alone
chips down the track and checks his shot, drive back to the bowler
tossed up on middle and punched to mid-on
clipped to the on side and there's confusion, Wade scampers back
stays back and punched it towards silly point
keeps Wade quiet again, he can only work it to the on side
Wade looking for the single to the on side  but he can't get it past the infield, it's a maiden
starts off with a half volley outside off and he drives firmly but sharply fielded at short cover
top marks for placement there! Full and wide outside off, he was bowling to a packed off side field but Clarke managed to get it past them, races past the covers
gets across and defends to the off side
Clarke's too strong on the off side, Cheema bowled this one shorter and still wide of the off stump, gets half forward and crashes it past backward point and cover
goes back and solidly punches it down to mid-off
god length on the off stump and punched softly to mid-off
spins away sharply and wade very awkwardly cuts it wide of point
drives a full delivery to mid-off and gets off the strike
clips it with the turn down to short midwicket
Clarke gets across his stumps early and clips it to midwicket
uses his feet again and pushes it to midwicket
tossed up slowly on the off stump and he pushes it down the track
starts off round the wicket, Wade softly clips it behind square on the on side
tossed up on middle and off and he drives down the ground to mid-on
comes well forward and blocks it out to cover
tossed up on the off stump and he works it with the turn gently to the on side
gets well forward and pushed towards cover point
strikes in his first over! Poor shot by Wade, he tried slogging him over midwicket, looked like the wrong 'un, the top edge swirled in the air and Misbah ran across and took it very close to Afridi
stays back and clips it with the turn to square leg
traps him on the pads but down the leg side, skids through
stays back and clips against the turn to midwicket
defends very close to pads and there's an appeal for an lbw because it may have hit the pad first, it did in fact, missing leg, Misbah decided not to review it
clips his pads again and missing leg, he's posing questions here Hafeez
gets forward and drives to the off side
pushes a full delivery through the line to mid-on
keeps a touch low and he punches it down to cover
full on the pads and clipped down to deep square leg
full on middle and leg and driven down to long-on
pushed through quicker on the pads and he whips him wide of midwicket for a couple, Afridi wasn't too pleased
tossed up on the off stump and defended
tossed up outside off and driven down to cover point
twinkle toes Clarke was down the track and adjusted well to cope with the turn and worked it to deep midwicket
goes back and punches it back to the bowler
stays back and works it against the turn down to midwicket
shuffles and clips it with the turn to square leg
the skidder has Hussey in trouble again, tossed up on middle and leg and it clips his pads outside the line of the leg stump
stays back and clips it with the turn to the on side
pushed through quicker and driven back to the bowler
driven firmly back to the bowler again, he's bowling them quicker
defends close to the pads and mistimes the drive down the pitch
Clarke comes down the pitch again and tucks it with the angle to deep square leg
used his feet and Afridi had him in a tangle there, pitched it shorter, outside edge to short third man

He's been given lbw and Hussey is reviewing it! Hussey is plumb in front I'm afraid, it landed on off and middle and straightened, Hussey was trapped on the back foot and the ball would have crashed onto the stumps, no inside edge, straightforward for Bowden
the doosra and Hussey did well not to touch that
shuffles and works it away down to fine leg
appeal for a bat-pad catch to short leg but that only hit the pad
the doosra squares up Clarke, it was a fuller delivery and Clarke didn't come forward, he moved across his stumps and was beaten
goes back and clips it with the turn to square leg
comes well forward and gets an inside edge to the pad on the drive
down the track and he clips it to the on side, can't beat Afridi
full and wide outside off and driven wide of mid-off
tossed up outside off and he pushes forward and shoulders arms
gives it a lot of flight outside off and Hussey is beaten on the drive, he should have put that away
a bit too short, he shuffles and works it with the turn to fine leg
pushed through quicker on the pads and clipped to the on side
outside edge and it evades Misbah! Came forward and he didn't read the doosra, just beat Misbah's dive at slip
tucked to the on side and he pinches a quick single
uses his feet and works it down to long-on

the spinners have really pulled things back here! Caught at slip, after inducing an edge off Clarle earlier in the over Ajmal gets one off Hussey, Hussey didn't read the doosra, he was forward to defend and the outside edge went straight to Misbah at first slip
full on the off stump and driven past a diving Afridi
lovely response, he was down the track and picked it from outside off and lofted him down the ground and wide of mid-on
tries to flick it and he ends up clipping it to his thigh
gets well forward and defends
stays back and punches it to the off side
stays back and punches it to mid-on
shuffles at the crease and clips it to the on side
stays back at the crease and defends the doosra
loses control of that and slides it wide down the leg side
